<exercise id="fs-id880486" type="ap-test-prep">
<problem id="fs-id1422697">
<para id="fs-id2000504">Why is the sound produced by a tambourine different from that produced by drums?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1716587">
<para id="fs-id544674">The sound energy coming out of an instrument depends on its size. The sound waves produced are relative to the size of the musical instrument. A smaller instrument such as a tambourine will produce a high-pitched sound (higher frequency, shorter wavelength), whereas a larger instrument such as a drum will produce a deeper sound (lower frequency, longer wavelength).</para>
</solution>
</exercise>

